@graceguo-supercat 

> Hi @betodealmeida In the new implementation, do you store actual query results in table? when query results are huge, it will be a problem for storage. and when user refreshing browser, do they download query results again?

No, I changed the backend so that sync queries are also stored in the results backend (if it's configured), similar to async queries. Then when we load the tab we load the results from the results backend.
